# Azure Blob Storage Module

This Terraform module creates Azure Blob Storage resources using a Storage Account, one or more containers, and optional lifecycle/CORS configuration.

## Features

- ✅ **Storage Account** - Create a secure StorageV2 account for blob workloads
- ✅ **Blob Containers** - Create one or many containers from a map input
- ✅ **Lifecycle Rules** - Tier and delete blobs/snapshots/versions automatically
- ✅ **Versioning & Change Feed** - Optional data protection and audit trail features
- ✅ **Retention Controls** - Blob and container soft-delete retention
- ✅ **CORS Support** - Optional CORS rules for browser-based clients
- ✅ **Security Defaults** - HTTPS-only and configurable public access behavior
- ✅ **Tagging** - Unified tagging with environment metadata

## Usage

### Call from another repository

Point `source` at this repo and the path under it (`//Azure/BlobStorage`). Pin **`ref` to a tag or commit** in production, not a branch that can change.

```hcl
module "blob_storage" {
  source = "git::https://github.com/saurabhrsahu/terraform-modules.git//Azure/BlobStorage?ref=main"
  # Use ?ref=v1.0.0 (or a commit SHA) once you tag releases
  # ...same inputs as in Basic Usage below
}
```

The **root** module where you call this must configure the **AzureRM** provider and authentication. This module only declares it needs `hashicorp/azurerm`.

```hcl
terraform {
  required_providers {
    azurerm = {
      source  = "hashicorp/azurerm"
      version = ">= 4.0.0, < 5.0.0"
    }
  }
}

provider "azurerm" {
  features {}
}
```

### Basic Usage

```hcl
module "blob_storage" {
  source = "../../modules/Azure/BlobStorage"

  resource_group_name  = "rg-app-dev"
  location             = "eastus"
  storage_account_name = "appdevblobstore01"

  containers = {
    data = {
      container_access_type = "private"
      metadata              = { purpose = "raw-data" }
    }
    archive = {
      container_access_type = "private"
    }
  }

  lifecycle_rules = [
    {
      name                       = "data-lifecycle"
      prefix_match               = ["data/"]
      tier_to_cool_after_days    = 30
      tier_to_archive_after_days = 180
      delete_after_days          = 365
    }
  ]

  tags = {
    team = "platform"
  }
}
```

## Inputs

| Name | Description | Type | Default | Required |
|------|-------------|------|---------|:--------:|
| `resource_group_name` | Resource group for the storage account | `string` | n/a | yes |
| `location` | Azure region | `string` | n/a | yes |
| `storage_account_name` | Globally unique storage account name | `string` | n/a | yes |
| `account_tier` | Storage account tier | `string` | `"Standard"` | no |
| `account_replication_type` | Replication type | `string` | `"LRS"` | no |
| `access_tier` | Blob access tier (`Hot`/`Cool`) | `string` | `"Hot"` | no |
| `containers` | Map of blob containers | `map(object)` | default one `data` container | no |
| `lifecycle_rules` | Blob lifecycle rules | `list(object)` | `[]` | no |
| `enable_versioning` | Enable blob versioning | `bool` | `true` | no |
| `enable_change_feed` | Enable change feed | `bool` | `false` | no |
| `allow_blob_public_access` | Allow public blob/container access | `bool` | `false` | no |
| `cors_rules` | CORS rules for blob service | `list(object)` | `[]` | no |
| `tags` | Additional resource tags | `map(string)` | `{}` | no |

## Outputs

| Name | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `storage_account_name` | Name of the storage account |
| `storage_account_id` | Resource ID of the storage account |
| `primary_blob_endpoint` | Primary blob endpoint URL |
| `container_names` | Names of created containers |
| `connection_info` | Basic account connection details and CLI example |
| `summary` | High-level module summary |

## Requirements

| Name | Version |
|------|---------|
| terraform | >= 1.3.0 |
| azurerm | >= 4.0.0, < 5.0.0 |

## Providers

| Name | Version |
|------|---------|
| azurerm | >= 4.0.0, < 5.0.0 |
